Cross-checking oracle (development only)
----------------------------------------
During development, fARM64's output is differentially compared against several
independent oracles: LLVM (llvm-mc / llvm-objdump), GNU binutils (objdump), and a
third-party AArch64 test corpus from Vector 35's "arch-arm64" project:

    arch-arm64
    Copyright 2020-2024 Vector 35 Inc.
    Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.

    A copy of the Apache License, Version 2.0 may be obtained at:
    http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0

That corpus is used ONLY as one development cross-check among several. It is read
locally, never shipped with fARM64, and is not authoritative: where it diverges
from the ARM ARM, fARM64 follows the spec and records the intentional divergence.
fARM64 is NOT a derivative work of arch-arm64; no fARM64 decode logic is ported,
transpiled, or otherwise copied from it.

Any vendored reference material under refs/ retains its own original license and
copyright (see, e.g., refs/arch-arm64-master/LICENSE) and is present for local
cross-checking only.
